cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.DC. 

The paper discusses a software engineering problem related to the correct usage of APIs, which suggests cs.SE as the most likely category. The proposed solution involves augmenting libraries with additional modules that check and enforce correctness policies, which could fall under cs.PL (programming languages) or cs.CR (cryptography and security). The paper also mentions the Android ecosystem as a specific context for evaluation, which could suggest cs.SY (systems and control) or cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing) as possible categories.
